{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c2eca9a9-f550-4423-b2e1-e249786e2b01","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**1. Replace the assembly reference with the MSTest NuGet package** in your `.csproj`:\n\n- Remove: `<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />`\n- Add: `<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.2\" />`\n\nYou can also update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (though MSTest v3 meta-package pulls it in).\n\n**2. No code changes needed** — your test file already uses `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting`, `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, and `Assert.*`, which are all preserved in MSTest v3.\n\n**Summary `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net462</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.2\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` v3 meta-package bundles the test framework, adapter, and test SDK together. Want me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"41bd3458-18d6-4c57-9381-c890f42737b8","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"581F:6969E:15EC88A:1747EAA:6A045FCF"},"id":"251aadc0-22e6-4ea1-b17d-758744973069","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:19.538Z","parentId":"0ac9f22b-8bf7-4e6a-ba38-a888e16a7720"}
